<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1801" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1801">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 319.1123L25/2.</note>
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-04">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 4, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Investigation of Colon mêlée is in progress by the military
                                authorities. Testimony thus far indicates it was started from
                                trifling cause and that killing of Langdon was reckless and
                                unprovoked. Langdon was in charge of our patrol. Policeman under
                                arrest was seen at a distance dodging back and forth from a blind
                                and shooting at our soldiers generally, including Langdon.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Price.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>